\begin_inset LatexCommand \label{eq:Rechenregeln-Lie-Klammern}

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{eqnarray}
L_{[f,g]}\alpha(x) & = & L_{f}L_{g}\alpha(x)-L_{g}L_{f}\alpha(x)\label{eq:Rechenregel-LK1}\\
{}[\alpha f,\beta g](x) & = & \alpha(x)\beta(x)[f,g](x)+\alpha(x)L_{f}\beta(x)\!\cdot\! g(x)-\beta(x)L_{g}\alpha(x)\!\cdot\! f(x).\label{eq:Rechenregel-LK2}\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Standard


\backslash
end{subequations}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
Zunï¿½hst gilt 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{eqnarray*}
L_{g}L_{f}\alpha(x) & = & \d L_{f}\alpha(x)\cdot g(x)\\
 & = & \left(\alpha^{\prime}(x)f^{\prime}(x)+f^{T}(x)\alpha^{\prime\prime}(x)\right)g(x)\\
 & = & \alpha^{\prime}(x)f^{\prime}(x)g(x)+f^{T}(x)\alpha^{\prime\prime}(x)g(x).\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

Vertauscht man die Reihenfolge der Vektorfelder, dann erhï¿½t man 
\begin_inset Formula \[
L_{f}L_{g}\alpha(x)=\alpha^{\prime}(x)g^{\prime}(x)f(x)+g^{T}(x)\alpha^{\prime\prime}(x)f(x).\]

\end_inset

Durch Symmetrie der Hessematrix\InsetSpace ~

\begin_inset Formula $\alpha^{\prime\prime}$
\end_inset

 vereinfacht sich die Differenz zu 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{eqnarray*}
L_{f}L_{g}\alpha(x)-L_{g}L_{f}\alpha(x) & = & \alpha^{\prime}(x)\left(g^{\prime}(x)f(x)-f^{\prime}(x)g(x)\right)\\
 & = & \alpha^{\prime}(x)\,[f,g](x)\\
 & = & L_{[f,g]}\alpha(x).\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

Damit ist Gl.\InsetSpace ~

\begin_inset LatexCommand \eqref{eq:Rechenregel-LK1}

\end_inset

