\begin_layout Standard
The existence conditions of the observer canonical form\InsetSpace ~

\begin_inset LatexCommand \prettyref{eq:nf}

\end_inset

 given in Sect.\InsetSpace ~

\begin_inset LatexCommand \ref{sec:Normal-Form-Observer}

\end_inset

 are rather restrictive, i.e., the observer error linearization can be applied
 only to a small class of systems.
 Several approximation methods have been suggested to circumvent this difficulty\InsetSpace ~

\begin_inset LatexCommand \cite{banaszuk97,lynch2001,moreno2005syncod}

\end_inset

.
 The main idea of these approaches is an appropriate decomposition of system\InsetSpace ~

\begin_inset LatexCommand \prettyref{eq:plant}

\end_inset

 into\InsetSpace ~

\begin_inset LatexCommand \prettyref{eq:plant-fg}

\end_inset

:
