\begin_layout Standard
We consider a driven van der Pol oscillator 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
\dot{x}_{1}=x_{2},\quad\dot{x}_{2}=-x_{1}+x_{2}(1-x_{1}^{2})+u,\quad y=x_{1}.\label{eq:vdp}\end{equation}

\end_inset

The conditions C1-C3 of Th.\InsetSpace ~

\begin_inset LatexCommand \ref{thm:existence}

\end_inset

 are fulfilled.
